<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1078,1175]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
In 
<collectingCountry box="[181,252,1079,1102]" name="South Korea" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Korea</collectingCountry>
, the Family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fischer" authorityYear="1817" box="[392,506,1078,1103]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Leporidae</taxonomicName>
contains two species of the Genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[901,968,1079,1102]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Lepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[901,968,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lepus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allen and Andrews" authorityYear="1913" box="[982,1114,1079,1102]" class="Mammalia" family="Ochotonidae" genus="Ochotona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="coreanus">
<emphasis box="[982,1114,1079,1102]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">L. coreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Radde" authorityYear="1861" box="[1168,1355,1078,1103]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Lepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mandshuricus">
<emphasis box="[1168,1355,1078,1103]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">L. mandshuricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. These two species have often been confused (
<bibRefCitation author="Jones &amp; Johnson" box="[591,851,1114,1139]" firstAuthor="Jones" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="359 - 407" refId="ref105827" refString="Jones Junior, J. K. &amp; Johnson, D. H. (1965) Synopsis of the lagomorphs and rodents of Korea. University of Kansas, Lawrence, pp. 359 - 407." type="book chapter" year="1965">Jones &amp; Johnson 1965</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1892" box="[870,1046,1116,1139]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Lepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="coreanus">
<emphasis box="[870,1046,1116,1139]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Lepus coreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is present in most of 
<collectingCountry box="[1291,1362,1115,1138]" name="South Korea" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Korea</collectingCountry>
, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Radde" authorityYear="1861" box="[151,337,1150,1175]" class="Mammalia" family="Leporidae" genus="Lepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lagomorpha" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mandshuricus">
<emphasis box="[151,337,1150,1175]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">L. mandshuricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occupies the northern border regions between 
<collectingCountry box="[862,931,1151,1174]" name="South Korea" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Korea</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1056,1150,1175]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
